tip.text: Love the chicken n veg (chicken teriyaki). Price is slightly expensive, but otherwise good was good and nothing to complain about. They are on ubereats and I regularly order from them.

I really like the aerial hoop and silk classes. Photo taken from @nicouze_yoga on Instagram.

The halibut baked in a bag with truffle mayo is amazing!!! Everyone has to try it! Quite a good portion.
Food is so so but ambience was really good! Great for dates.

tip.text: Great place. Love the vanoffie pie! Password for wifi is buddhalove if anyone hasn't change it.
Naughty fries is the bomb! The fries is the best!! Ordered a burning man burger and it was just okay. Nothing special.
The salmon set was pretty good!! Love the tempura and boiled salmon. The side dishes were mediocre.
Food here is good and staff are friendly. Love the spicy dumpling and liu sha bao!
It's a joy for any dog lovers to go see the dogs. So cute!
Steak has a large portion, meat was soft, but was quite tasteless.
Crispy suckling pig is one of my fave!!
It will take about 10-12 tapas to feed 2 people. So don't come with too empty of a stomach.
Iberica joselito is one of those more unique dishes I've tried. It's with tomato essence.
The food here is really unique and very nice!!!!! A tad expensive, but it's good to try once in a while.
Good service, but I wasn't impressed with the decor, the chicken wrap nor the hot chocolate. I prefer the hot chocolate at the d'good cafe.
Service, price, food here is much better than d good cafe. Prefer here. Although there are no swings here, the place is much more spacious!
The food a a tad expensive for the taste and ambiance. English breakfast set is $16.50, pretty long waiting time. Bread is unique, but everything else is nothing special.
Hot chocolate is really good, ok price.
The meat platter is quite a mouthful! Great for large gatherings. Good food!
The charashi bowl is really good. Cost $25, and I feel that the price is reasonable because of the amount of ingredients it has.

Not full from the salad and it tasted mediocre. About $18 with service charge.

The yuzu umeshu tastes like orange juice with vodka. Definitely the cocktails are not good.
The mini burgers are good. Value for money tapas wise.
Compared between the mushroom dishes, the king oyster is much better than assorted mushrooms tempura.
The food here is average. But experience is good. Jia xiang he tao chicken is the best among what we ate.

Out of the 3 cakes I've had, I liked the oreo cheesecake the most, followed by mille crepe cake then blueberry yogurt cake.
Matcha tiramisu for rmb$35. Quite unique.
Good carrot cake! Slightly dry but love the cheese topping. Comes with a side of yogurt.

tip.text: Singapore sling is very tasty!!!
Curry mee is not bad.
Brownie doesn't come with ice cream. Though you could definitely top up $4 for vanilla ice cream. Really good!
Bacon and waffles, sweet and savory. My kind of thing.
Pineapple soju is good!! My friend says it is better than watermelon soju.
Yangnyum chicken is really good!! Much better than spicy up. Spicy up half chicken is 18, chicken wings are 12 for 4.
Ice chocolate is moderate. Not sweet enough. Had to add sugar.
My favourites were the chocolate mousse and the bone marrow butter bread.
Miso cod is decent. Quite fresh. But the pumpkin wasn't fresh, salad was good.
Truffle fries is really huge. Good for sharing if you have a large party. But I find that there's not enough truffle oil in it.
The sandwich is very mediocre, tomatoes are not fresh, served with potatoe chips and the salad is bad. If I wanted chip, I would have gone to cold storage.
Green tea tofu cheesecake. Not wobbly, too hard and cannot taste any green tea flavor.
Cake is 7.50, quite a substantial portion. Ok but not worth the price. They were also out of a lot of many items on their menu.

tip.text: The chairs that I has was "truck shop", it's non sweeten and you can add your own sugar.
Decor is cool, but the chairs are not that comfy.
I paid $7.50 for their lunch special. One chicken Masala croissant and a drink. The croissant is kinda dry though. Wish they had some sauce to top on it.
Out of all that I've ordered, chilli fries is the best! A tad spicy but I like it! Good place to chill!
They don't have desserts on their menu but they can bring it up from the restaurant on the first floor.

tip.text: Bulgogi set is really good!! Love it. Have been here twice this week. I like the food. the side dishes are not that great though.
Good fast wifi here. But I don't get why my yuzu soda is $7 while the earl grey is $9. But I'll come back here if I want to work in a cafe.

tip.text: The bento set is $25. It's worth the price! Tasty, good variety! There's fruits, sashimi, miso soup and tempura. Sashimi is fresh!

formattedAddress: The Fullerton Hotel, Lobby (1 Fullerton Square)

tip.text: The staff were friendly, but highly pushy! That's expected from groupon, but they became unethical after I declined all the packages. They would just changed the terms of the groupon randomly.
Gula malaka cookie for $1.60. Very unique and tasty!!

For 9.80 on a regular plate, you get 2 protein and 4 sides.They usually give 2 huge slices of smoked salmon! I think that has the greatest value. When there's a queue it might take awhile to be served
The ambience of the place is not that great, often nobody clears up the tables. But the desserts are to die for! I had it in Japan before and felt like the food standard is the same.
Good food, decent service & reasonably priced. Highly recommended! Except it gets a little bit hot inside and you'll get sweaty. Don't recommend it for dates if you perspire a lot! Lol.
Buffalo wings are really tasty at only $15. But almost every other food was sold out (tapas, salads, soups, main course). But overall, good place to chill out.

formattedAddress: #01-04, The Arts House (1 Old Parliament Lane)

tip.text: I try to avoid peak hours as I don't want to queue. But since it's 24hours now; it's great for supper lovers!! Food is really good! Apart from the carrot cake, everything else is really good!
I find it expensive because the sandwich is $12 and pre prepared on the shelves - they just take it out to toast it. But it's good because it wasn't really crowded with loads of table space.
Really good customer service!! Cakes were very nice! I spent $9 on a cake and thought it was worth it!

formattedAddress: The Fullerton Hotel, Lobby (1 Fullerton Square)

tip.text: I really like the French toast. Very different from what you would expect! Good for people with sweet tooth! Like the vibe of the place!
I enjoyed the salmon eggs Benedict thoroughly especially with the Greek yogurt, the waffles was nice but not that special! Good place! Will recommend.
